# Educational Notebook : USCRN Legacy Pairs, GHCNv4 RAW. 
# 8 golden USCRN pairs used
import requests
import tarfile
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import io

# === Settings ===
baseline_start = 1920
baseline_end = 1940
min_months = 11
start_year = 1900
end_year = 2024
smoothing_frac = 0.13

# === Step 1: Download and extract
url = "https://www.ncei.noaa.gov/pub/data/ghcn/v4/ghcnm.tavg.latest.qcu.tar.gz"
response = requests.get(url, stream=True)
tar_bytes = io.BytesIO(response.content)

# Station pairs, the magnificent 8 USCRN (HUSCRN) with more than 90 years data.
pairs = [
    ("USC00012813", "USW00063869"),
    ("USC00294426", "USW00003074"),
    ("USC00402202", "USW00063855"),
    ("USC00250030", "USW00094077"),
    ("USC00018385", "USW00073801"),
    ("USC00380764", "USW00063826"),
    ("USC00013160", "USW00063892"),
    ("USC00348501", "USW00053926")
]
station_ids = {sid for p in pairs for sid in p}

# === Step 2: Extract and grep lines
filtered_lines = []
with tarfile.open(fileobj=tar_bytes, mode="r:gz") as tar:
    dat_member = next(m for m in tar.getmembers() if m.name.endswith(".qcu.dat"))
    dat_file = tar.extractfile(dat_member)
    for line in dat_file:
        sid = line[0:11].decode("utf-8").strip()
        if sid in station_ids and line[15:19].decode("utf-8") == "TAVG":
            filtered_lines.append(line.decode("utf-8"))

# === Step 3: Parse temperature data
records = []
for line in filtered_lines:
    sid = line[0:11].strip()
    year = int(line[11:15])
    if year < start_year or year > end_year:
        continue
    monthly = [int(line[19 + m*8:24 + m*8]) for m in range(12)]
    monthly = [v / 100.0 if v != -9999 else None for v in monthly]
    if sum(v is not None for v in monthly) >= min_months:
        avg = np.mean([v for v in monthly if v is not None])
        records.append([year, avg, sid])

df = pd.DataFrame(records, columns=["year", "tavg", "station_id"])

# === Step 4: Build per-pair anomalies (with pairwise baseline subtraction)
pairwise_anomalies = []

for legacy_id, uscrn_id in pairs:
    df_legacy = df[df["station_id"] == legacy_id].set_index("year")
    df_uscrn = df[df["station_id"] == uscrn_id].set_index("year")
    all_years = sorted(set(df_legacy.index).union(df_uscrn.index))
    combined = []
    for y in all_years:
        temps = []
        if y in df_legacy.index:
            temps.append(df_legacy.loc[y, "tavg"])
        if y in df_uscrn.index:
            temps.append(df_uscrn.loc[y, "tavg"])
        if temps:
            combined.append([y, np.mean(temps)])
    df_pair = pd.DataFrame(combined, columns=["year", "tavg"])
    
    # Compute pair-specific baseline
    base = df_pair[(df_pair["year"] >= baseline_start) & (df_pair["year"] <= baseline_end)]
    if not base.empty:
        baseline_mean = base["tavg"].mean()
        df_pair["anomaly"] = df_pair["tavg"] - baseline_mean
        pairwise_anomalies.append(df_pair[["year", "anomaly"]])

# === Step 5: Aggregate anomalies across all pairs (after baseline subtraction)
df_all = pd.concat(pairwise_anomalies)
df_agg = df_all.groupby("year")["anomaly"].mean().reset_index()

# === Step 6: LOESS smoothing
loess = sm.nonparametric.lowess(endog=df_agg["anomaly"],
                                exog=df_agg["year"], frac=smoothing_frac)

# === Step 7: Plot (dark background, styled)
plt.style.use('dark_background')
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
ax.plot(df_agg["year"], df_agg["anomaly"], label="Aggregated Anomaly", color='cyan',
        linewidth=2, marker='o', markersize=4, alpha=0.9)
ax.plot(loess[:, 0], loess[:, 1], color='cyan', linewidth=4, alpha=0.6, label="LOESS Trend")

ax.set_title("Historic USCRN Temperature Anomalies (Baseline 1920–1940) – GHCN RAW", fontsize=15, weight='bold')
ax.set_xlabel("Year", fontsize=12)
ax.set_ylabel("Temperature Anomaly (°C)", fontsize=12)
ax.set_ylim(-2, 3)
ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
ax.legend(loc="upper left", fontsize=10)

fig.text(0.01, -0.12,
         "Data Source: GHCN v4.0.1 QCU – NOAA\n"
         "Yearly averages computed from >=11 months per year.\n"
         "Anomalies computed per station pair using 1920–1940 baseline.\n"
         "Then averaged across all 8 pairs.\n",
         fontsize=9, color='white')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# --- Function to Load and Process GHCN Data ---
# (Code remains the same)
def load_and_process_ghcn(data_url, file_suffix, needed_ids, s_year, e_year, m_months):
    print(f"\n--- Processing: {data_url.split('/')[-1]} ---")
    df_raw = pd.DataFrame(columns=["year", "tavg", "station_id"]); dat_member_name="Unknown"
    try:
        print(f"Downloading data..."); response = requests.get(data_url, stream=True, timeout=60); response.raise_for_status(); tar_bytes = io.BytesIO(response.content)
        print(f"Extracting and filtering...")
        with tarfile.open(fileobj=tar_bytes, mode="r:gz") as tar:
            dat_members = [m for m in tar.getmembers() if m.name.endswith(file_suffix)];
            if not dat_members: raise ValueError(f"No {file_suffix} file in tar.")
            dat_member = dat_members[0]; dat_member_name = dat_member.name; print(f"Extracting from: {dat_member_name}")
            dat_file = tar.extractfile(dat_member); filtered_lines = []
            for line_bytes in dat_file:
                 try: line_str = line_bytes.decode("utf-8", errors='replace'); sid = line_str[0:11].strip()
                 except: continue
                 if sid in needed_ids and line_str[15:19] == "TAVG": filtered_lines.append(line_str)
        print(f"Found {len(filtered_lines)} relevant TAVG lines."); print(f"Parsing temperature data ({s_year}-{e_year})...")
        records = []
        for line in filtered_lines:
            try:
                sid = line[0:11].strip(); year = int(line[11:15])
                if year < s_year or year > e_year: continue
                monthly_temps = [np.nan]*12; valid_months = 0
                for m in range(12):
                    val_str = line[19 + m*8 : 24 + m*8].strip()
                    if val_str and val_str != "-9999": temp = int(val_str) / 100.0; monthly_temps[m]=temp; valid_months += 1
                if valid_months >= m_months:
                    yearly_avg = np.nanmean(monthly_temps)
                    if not np.isnan(yearly_avg): records.append([year, yearly_avg, sid])
            except: pass
        df_raw = pd.DataFrame(records, columns=["year", "tavg", "station_id"])
        print(f"Parsed {len(df_raw)} valid yearly averages (min_months={m_months}).")
    except Exception as e: print(f"Data Loading/Processing Error: {e}")
    return df_raw, dat_member_name

# --- Function to Calculate Anomalies ---
# (Code remains the same - RELAXED baseline AND RELAXED COVERAGE logic)
def calculate_anomalies(df_raw_data, series_station_ids, settings_dict):
    """Calculates anomalies with RELAXED baseline AND RELAXED COVERAGE."""
    results = { 'anomalies': {}, 'stations_used': {}, 'counts': {} }
    baseline_s = settings_dict['baseline_start']; baseline_e = settings_dict['baseline_end']
    start_y = settings_dict['start_year']; end_y = settings_dict['end_year']
    orig_pairs = settings_dict['original_pairs']
    # --- H8 --- (Logic unchanged)
    print(f"\nCalculating H8 USCRN Anomalies (Baseline {baseline_s}-{baseline_e})")
    h8_ids = series_station_ids['H8']; results['stations_used']['H8'] = list(h8_ids)
    original_pairwise_anomalies = []; df_raw_original = df_raw_data[df_raw_data['station_id'].isin(h8_ids)]
    h8_pairs_with_baseline_data = 0
    if not df_raw_original.empty:
        for legacy_id, uscrn_id in orig_pairs:
            df_legacy = df_raw_original[df_raw_original["station_id"] == legacy_id].set_index("year")["tavg"]
            df_uscrn = df_raw_original[df_raw_original["station_id"] == uscrn_id].set_index("year")["tavg"]
            df_pair_tavg = pd.concat([df_legacy, df_uscrn], axis=1).mean(axis=1, skipna=True).reset_index()
            df_pair_tavg.columns = ["year", "tavg"]; df_pair_tavg = df_pair_tavg.dropna(subset=['tavg'])
            base_vals = df_pair_tavg[(df_pair_tavg["year"] >= baseline_s) & (df_pair_tavg["year"] <= baseline_e)]["tavg"]
            if base_vals.notna().any():
                 baseline_mean = base_vals.mean()
                 df_pair_tavg["anomaly"] = df_pair_tavg["tavg"] - baseline_mean
                 original_pairwise_anomalies.append(df_pair_tavg[["year", "anomaly"]])
                 h8_pairs_with_baseline_data += 1
        if original_pairwise_anomalies:
            df_all_original = pd.concat(original_pairwise_anomalies); df_agg_original = df_all_original.groupby("year")["anomaly"].mean().reset_index()
            results['anomalies']['H8'] = df_agg_original; results['counts']['H8'] = h8_pairs_with_baseline_data
            print(f"Aggregated H8 USCRN from {h8_pairs_with_baseline_data} pairs with valid baseline data.")
    if 'H8' not in results['anomalies']: results['anomalies']['H8'] = pd.DataFrame(columns=['year', 'anomaly'])
    if 'H8' not in results['counts']: results['counts']['H8'] = 0
    # --- BU --- (Logic unchanged - relaxed coverage & baseline)
    for series_name, bu_ids in [('LowBU', series_station_ids['LowBU']), ('HighBU', series_station_ids['HighBU'])]:
        print(f"\nCalculating {series_name} US Anomalies (Baseline {baseline_s}-{baseline_e})")
        df_raw_bu = df_raw_data[df_raw_data['station_id'].isin(bu_ids)]; stations_meeting_coverage = []
        final_bu_station_count = 0; results['stations_used'][series_name] = []
        if not df_raw_bu.empty:
            grouped = df_raw_bu.groupby('station_id'); total_years_in_range = end_y - start_y + 1
            min_years_required_for_coverage = int(total_years_in_range * 0.90)
            for station_id, group in grouped:
                 if (group['year'].nunique() >= min_years_required_for_coverage and
                     group['year'].min() <= start_y + 10 and group['year'].max() >= end_y - 10):
                      stations_meeting_coverage.append(station_id)
            print(f"Found {len(stations_meeting_coverage)} {series_name} stations meeting coverage criteria (>= {min_years_required_for_coverage} years).")
            if stations_meeting_coverage:
                df_subset = df_raw_bu[df_raw_bu['station_id'].isin(stations_meeting_coverage)].copy()
                baseline_data = df_subset[(df_subset['year'] >= baseline_s) & (df_subset['year'] <= baseline_e)]
                station_baselines_mean = baseline_data.groupby('station_id')['tavg'].mean()
                stations_with_baseline = station_baselines_mean.dropna().index; final_stations_used = list(stations_with_baseline)
                results['stations_used'][series_name] = final_stations_used; final_bu_station_count = len(final_stations_used)
                if final_bu_station_count > 0:
                    df_subset_final = df_subset[df_subset['station_id'].isin(final_stations_used)].copy()
                    print(f"Calculating {series_name} anomalies for {final_bu_station_count} stations with valid baseline data.")
                    df_subset_final['baseline_mean'] = df_subset_final['station_id'].map(station_baselines_mean.dropna())
                    df_subset_final['anomaly'] = df_subset_final['tavg'] - df_subset_final['baseline_mean']
                    df_subset_final = df_subset_final.dropna(subset=['anomaly'])
                    df_agg_bu = df_subset_final.groupby('year')['anomaly'].mean().reset_index()
                    results['anomalies'][series_name] = df_agg_bu; results['counts'][series_name] = final_bu_station_count
                    print(f"Aggregated {series_name} anomalies.")
        if series_name not in results['anomalies']: results['anomalies'][series_name] = pd.DataFrame(columns=['year', 'anomaly'])
        if series_name not in results['counts']: results['counts'][series_name] = 0
        if series_name not in results['stations_used']: results['stations_used'][series_name] = []
    return results

# --- Function to Plot Anomalies for one data type ---
# (Code remains the same)
def plot_anomalies(anomaly_results, data_type_label, df_meta_idx, settings_dict, filename):
    """Generates the anomaly plot with basemap for QCU or QCF and displays it."""
    print(f"\n--- Plotting {data_type_label} Anomalies ---")
    plt.style.use('dark_background'); fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 7))
    counts = anomaly_results['counts']; anomalies = anomaly_results['anomalies']; stations_used = anomaly_results['stations_used']
    plot_title = f"US GHCN {data_type_label} Anomalies (Baseline {settings_dict['baseline_start']}–{settings_dict['baseline_end']})"
    title_suffix = []; any_series_plotted = False
    colors = settings_dict['plot_colors']; markers = settings_dict['plot_markers']
    linewidth_raw = settings_dict[f"{data_type_label.lower()}_linewidth_raw"]; linewidth_smooth = settings_dict[f"{data_type_label.lower()}_linewidth_smooth"]
    for series_name in ['H8', 'LowBU', 'HighBU']: # Plotting loop unchanged
        df_agg = anomalies.get(series_name); count = counts.get(series_name, 0)
        if df_agg is not None and not df_agg.empty and count > 0:
            try:
                series_label_base = f"{series_name}"; series_label_count = f"N={count}"
                if series_name == 'LowBU': series_label_base = f"Low BU US ({settings_dict['low_bu_min']}-{settings_dict['low_bu_max']}%)"
                if series_name == 'HighBU': series_label_base = f"High BU US (>{settings_dict['high_bu_min']}%)"
                if series_name == 'H8': series_label_count = f"N={count} pairs"
                df_clean = df_agg.dropna(subset=['year', 'anomaly'])
                if len(df_clean) > 5:
                    loess = sm.nonparametric.lowess(endog=df_clean["anomaly"], exog=df_clean["year"], frac=settings_dict['smoothing_frac'])
                    if loess.ndim == 2 and loess.shape[1] == 2: ax.plot(loess[:, 0], loess[:, 1], color=colors[series_name], linewidth=linewidth_smooth, alpha=0.9, label=f"{series_label_base} LOESS")
                ax.plot(df_agg["year"], df_agg["anomaly"], label=f"{series_label_base} Anomaly ({series_label_count})", color=colors[series_name], linewidth=linewidth_raw, marker=markers[series_name], markersize=3, alpha=0.7, linestyle='-' if linewidth_raw > 0 else 'None')
                any_series_plotted = True; title_suffix.append(f"{series_name} N={count}")
            except Exception as e: print(f"Plotting Error ({data_type_label} - {series_name}): {e}")
    # Axis setup and map inlay unchanged...
    ax.set_title(f"{plot_title} - {' | '.join(title_suffix)}", fontsize=13, weight='bold', color='white')
    ax.set_xlabel("Year", fontsize=12, color='white'); ax.set_ylabel("Temperature Anomaly (°C)", fontsize=12, color='white')
    ax.tick_params(axis='x', colors='white'); ax.tick_params(axis='y', colors='white')
    min_lim = np.inf; max_lim = -np.inf
    if any_series_plotted:
         for s in ['H8', 'LowBU', 'HighBU']:
              df = anomalies.get(s);
              if df is not None and 'anomaly' in df and df['anomaly'].notna().any(): min_lim=min(min_lim,df['anomaly'].min(skipna=True)); max_lim=max(max_lim,df['anomaly'].max(skipna=True))
         if np.isfinite(min_lim) and np.isfinite(max_lim): ax.set_ylim(min_lim - 0.5, max_lim + 0.5)
         else: ax.set_ylim(-2.5, 3.5)
    else: ax.set_ylim(-2.5, 3.5)
    ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3, color='gray'); ax.axhline(0, color='white', linestyle='--', linewidth=0.8, alpha=0.5)
    box = ax.get_position(); ax.set_position([box.x0, box.y0, box.width * 0.75, box.height])
    handles, labels = ax.get_legend_handles_labels();
    if handles: ax.legend(handles, labels, loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(1.02, 1), borderaxespad=0., fontsize=9, facecolor='black', edgecolor='white')
    if basemap_available and df_meta_idx is not None:
        stations_to_map = [id for series in ['H8', 'LowBU', 'HighBU'] if stations_used.get(series) for id in stations_used[series]]
        if stations_to_map:
             # print(f"Adding basemap inlay for {data_type_label}...") # Optional print
             try:
                 ax_inset = fig.add_axes([0.78, 0.15, 0.20, 0.20]); m = Basemap(projection='lcc', resolution='l', lat_0=39, lon_0=-96, llcrnrlon=-125, llcrnrlat=23, urcrnrlon=-65, urcrnrlat=50, ax=ax_inset)
                 m.drawcoastlines(color='0.6',lw=0.5); m.drawcountries(color='0.6',lw=0.5); m.drawstates(color='0.5',lw=0.5); m.fillcontinents(color='0.2', lake_color='0.1'); marker_size = 10
                 for series_name in ['H8', 'LowBU', 'HighBU']:
                     ids = stations_used.get(series_name)
                     if ids: coords = df_meta_idx.reindex(ids).dropna(subset=[settings['meta_lat_col'], settings['meta_lon_col']])
                     if not coords.empty: x, y = m(coords[settings['meta_lon_col']].values, coords[settings['meta_lat_col']].values); m.scatter(x, y, s=marker_size, color=colors[series_name], marker=markers[series_name], alpha=0.8, zorder=5+list(colors.keys()).index(series_name))
                 ax_inset.set_title("Station Locations", fontsize=9, color='white')
             except Exception as map_e: print(f"Basemap inlay Error: {map_e}")
    # Footnote setup unchanged...
    data_source_filename = f"ghcnm.tavg.latest.{data_type_label.lower()}.dat"; meta_filename = metadata_url.split('/')[-1]
    fig.text(0.01, -0.03, f"Data: US Stations from GHCN v4 ({data_source_filename}) | Metadata: {meta_filename}\nYearly avg >= {settings['min_months']} months/yr | Baseline: {settings['baseline_start']}–{settings['baseline_end']} | Coverage: {settings['start_year']}-{settings['end_year']}\nH8: Avg({counts.get('H8', 0)} pairs) | LowBU: Avg(N={counts.get('LowBU', 0)}, {settings['low_bu_min']}-{settings['low_bu_max']}%) | HighBU: Avg(N={counts.get('HighBU', 0)}, >{settings['high_bu_min']}%)", fontsize=8.5, color='white', va='top')
    try: plt.savefig(filename, dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight', facecolor='black'); print(f"Plot saved as {filename}")
    except Exception as e: print(f"\nError saving plot {filename}: {e}")
    plt.show(); plt.close(fig)

# --- Function to Plot Comparison (Static Only) ---
# (Code remains the same)
def plot_comparison(qcu_results, qcf_results, settings_dict, plot_filename):
    """Generates a static comparison plot of LOESS curves (saves and shows)."""
    print("\n--- Plotting QCU vs QCF LOESS Comparison (Static) ---")
    plt.style.use('dark_background'); fig_comp, ax_comp = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    qcu_anomalies = qcu_results['anomalies']; qcf_anomalies = qcf_results['anomalies']
    colors = settings_dict['plot_colors']; min_year_overall = settings_dict['start_year']; max_year_overall = settings_dict['end_year']
    min_anomaly_overall = np.inf; max_anomaly_overall = -np.inf; loess_data = {}; any_data = False
    for dt_label, anomalies_dict in [('QCU', qcu_anomalies), ('QCF', qcf_anomalies)]: # LOESS Calculation unchanged
        loess_data[dt_label] = {}
        for series_name in ['H8', 'LowBU', 'HighBU']:
            df_agg = anomalies_dict.get(series_name)
            if df_agg is not None and not df_agg.empty and 'anomaly' in df_agg and df_agg['anomaly'].notna().any():
                 df_clean = df_agg.dropna(subset=['year', 'anomaly'])
                 if len(df_clean) > 5:
                     try: loess = sm.nonparametric.lowess(endog=df_clean["anomaly"], exog=df_clean["year"], frac=settings_dict['smoothing_frac'])
                     except Exception as e: print(f"LOESS Error ({dt_label}-{series_name}): {e}"); continue
                     if loess.ndim == 2 and loess.shape[1] == 2: loess_data[dt_label][series_name] = {'years': loess[:, 0], 'anomalies': loess[:, 1]}; min_anomaly_overall = min(min_anomaly_overall, loess[:, 1].min()); max_anomaly_overall = max(max_anomaly_overall, loess[:, 1].max()); any_data = True
    if not any_data: print("No LOESS data for comparison."); plt.close(fig_comp); return
    if np.isfinite(min_anomaly_overall) and np.isfinite(max_anomaly_overall): min_anomaly_overall -= 0.2; max_anomaly_overall += 0.2
    else: min_anomaly_overall = -2.0; max_anomaly_overall = 3.0
    plot_lines = []; plot_labels = [] # Plotting loop unchanged
    for dt_label, line_style, lw in [('QCU', settings_dict['qcu_linestyle'], settings_dict['qcu_linewidth_smooth']), ('QCF', settings_dict['qcf_linestyle'], settings_dict['qcf_linewidth_smooth'])]:
        for series_name in ['H8', 'LowBU', 'HighBU']:
             if loess_data.get(dt_label, {}).get(series_name): data = loess_data[dt_label][series_name]; line, = ax_comp.plot(data['years'], data['anomalies'], color=colors[series_name], linestyle=line_style, linewidth=lw, alpha=0.9); label = f"{series_name} ({dt_label})"; plot_lines.append(line); plot_labels.append(label)
    # Axis setup unchanged...
    ax_comp.set_title(f"Comparison of LOESS Smoothed US Anomalies (QCU vs QCF)", fontsize=14, weight='bold', color='white')
    ax_comp.set_xlabel("Year", fontsize=12, color='white'); ax_comp.set_ylabel("Smoothed Temperature Anomaly (°C)", fontsize=12, color='white')
    ax_comp.tick_params(axis='x', colors='white'); ax_comp.tick_params(axis='y', colors='white'); ax_comp.set_xlim(min_year_overall, max_year_overall); ax_comp.set_ylim(min_anomaly_overall, max_anomaly_overall)
    ax_comp.grid(True, alpha=0.3, color='gray'); ax_comp.axhline(0, color='white', linestyle=':', linewidth=0.8, alpha=0.5)
    if plot_lines: ax_comp.legend(plot_lines, plot_labels, loc='upper left', fontsize=9, facecolor='black', edgecolor='white', ncol=2)
    # Footnotes unchanged...
    meta_filename = metadata_url.split('/')[-1]; fig_comp.text(0.01, -0.03, f"Data: GHCN v4 QCU & QCF | Metadata: {meta_filename}\nSmoothed anomaly comparison | LOESS frac={settings_dict['smoothing_frac']} | Baseline: {settings_dict['baseline_start']}–{settings_dict['baseline_end']}\nCoverage: {settings_dict['start_year']}-{settings_dict['end_year']} | Derived from stations meeting criteria in individual plots.", fontsize=8.5, color='white', va='top')
    try: fig_comp.savefig(plot_filename, dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight', facecolor='black'); print(f"Comparison plot saved as {plot_filename}")
    except Exception as e: print(f"\nError saving comparison plot {plot_filename}: {e}")
    plt.show(); plt.close(fig_comp)


# --- CORRECTED Function to Plot Difference (using RAW temps) ---
def plot_difference(df_raw_qcu, df_raw_qcf, qcu_results, qcf_results, settings_dict, plot_filename):
    """Generates a static plot of LOESS smoothed difference between
       RAW QCF and QCU temperatures (adjustment), independent of baseline.
    """
    print("\n--- Plotting QCF - QCU Adjustment (Smoothed Raw Temperature Difference) ---")
    plt.style.use('dark_background')
    fig_diff, ax_diff = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))

    colors = settings_dict['plot_colors']
    min_year_overall = settings_dict['start_year']
    max_year_overall = settings_dict['end_year']
    min_diff_overall = np.inf
    max_diff_overall = -np.inf
    loess_diff_data = {}
    any_diff_data = False
    common_station_counts = {} # Store N for common stations

    # --- BU Series: Difference based on common stations raw averages ---
    for series_name in ['LowBU', 'HighBU']:
        print(f"Processing raw difference for {series_name} using common stations...")
        stations_qcu = set(qcu_results['stations_used'].get(series_name, []))
        stations_qcf = set(qcf_results['stations_used'].get(series_name, []))
        common_stations = list(stations_qcu.intersection(stations_qcf))
        common_station_counts[series_name] = len(common_stations)
        print(f"  Found {len(common_stations)} common stations for {series_name}.")

        if not common_stations or df_raw_qcu is None or df_raw_qcf is None:
            print(f"  Skipping {series_name} difference: No common stations or missing raw data.")
            loess_diff_data[series_name] = None; continue

        # Filter raw data for common stations
        df_common_qcu_raw = df_raw_qcu[df_raw_qcu['station_id'].isin(common_stations)].copy()
        df_common_qcf_raw = df_raw_qcf[df_raw_qcf['station_id'].isin(common_stations)].copy()

        # Calculate average raw tavg for common stations
        df_avg_raw_qcu = df_common_qcu_raw.groupby('year')['tavg'].mean().reset_index()
        df_avg_raw_qcf = df_common_qcf_raw.groupby('year')['tavg'].mean().reset_index()

        # Merge and calculate raw difference
        df_merged_raw = pd.merge(df_avg_raw_qcf, df_avg_raw_qcu, on='year', suffixes=('_qcf', '_qcu'), how='inner')
        if not df_merged_raw.empty:
            df_merged_raw['difference'] = df_merged_raw['tavg_qcf'] - df_merged_raw['tavg_qcu']
            # Calculate LOESS on the raw difference
            df_clean = df_merged_raw.dropna(subset=['year', 'difference'])
            if len(df_clean) > 5:
                try:
                    loess_diff = sm.nonparametric.lowess(endog=df_clean["difference"], exog=df_clean["year"], frac=settings_dict['smoothing_frac'])
                    if loess_diff.ndim == 2 and loess_diff.shape[1] == 2:
                        loess_diff_data[series_name] = {'years': loess_diff[:, 0], 'difference': loess_diff[:, 1]}
                        min_diff_overall = min(min_diff_overall, loess_diff[:, 1].min()); max_diff_overall = max(max_diff_overall, loess_diff[:, 1].max())
                        any_diff_data = True
                except Exception as e: print(f"  LOESS Error ({series_name} raw diff): {e}")
        # else: print(f"  No common years found for avg raw {series_name}.") # Optional info

    # --- H8 Series: Difference based on pairwise raw averages ---
    print(f"Processing raw difference for H8 using pairwise averages...")
    series_name = 'H8'
    pairwise_raw_diffs = []
    pairs_used_count = 0
    if df_raw_qcu is not None and df_raw_qcf is not None:
        df_raw_qcu_h8 = df_raw_qcu[df_raw_qcu['station_id'].isin(station_id_groups['H8'])]
        df_raw_qcf_h8 = df_raw_qcf[df_raw_qcf['station_id'].isin(station_id_groups['H8'])]

        for legacy_id, uscrn_id in settings_dict['original_pairs']:
            # Calculate QCU pairwise raw avg
            df_legacy_qcu = df_raw_qcu_h8[df_raw_qcu_h8["station_id"] == legacy_id].set_index("year")["tavg"]
            df_uscrn_qcu = df_raw_qcu_h8[df_raw_qcu_h8["station_id"] == uscrn_id].set_index("year")["tavg"]
            df_pair_tavg_qcu = pd.concat([df_legacy_qcu, df_uscrn_qcu], axis=1).mean(axis=1, skipna=True)

            # Calculate QCF pairwise raw avg
            df_legacy_qcf = df_raw_qcf_h8[df_raw_qcf_h8["station_id"] == legacy_id].set_index("year")["tavg"]
            df_uscrn_qcf = df_raw_qcf_h8[df_raw_qcf_h8["station_id"] == uscrn_id].set_index("year")["tavg"]
            df_pair_tavg_qcf = pd.concat([df_legacy_qcf, df_uscrn_qcf], axis=1).mean(axis=1, skipna=True)

            # Combine and calculate difference for the pair
            df_pair_diff = (df_pair_tavg_qcf - df_pair_tavg_qcu).dropna().reset_index()
            df_pair_diff.columns = ['year', 'difference']

            if not df_pair_diff.empty:
                pairwise_raw_diffs.append(df_pair_diff)
                pairs_used_count += 1

        if pairwise_raw_diffs:
            df_all_h8_diff = pd.concat(pairwise_raw_diffs)
            df_agg_h8_diff = df_all_h8_diff.groupby("year")["difference"].mean().reset_index()
            # Calculate LOESS on the aggregated raw difference
            df_clean = df_agg_h8_diff.dropna(subset=['year', 'difference'])
            if len(df_clean) > 5:
                 try:
                     loess_diff = sm.nonparametric.lowess(endog=df_clean["difference"], exog=df_clean["year"], frac=settings_dict['smoothing_frac'])
                     if loess_diff.ndim == 2 and loess_diff.shape[1] == 2:
                         loess_diff_data[series_name] = {'years': loess_diff[:, 0], 'difference': loess_diff[:, 1]}
                         min_diff_overall = min(min_diff_overall, loess_diff[:, 1].min()); max_diff_overall = max(max_diff_overall, loess_diff[:, 1].max())
                         any_diff_data = True
                 except Exception as e: print(f"  LOESS Error (H8 raw diff): {e}")
            print(f"  Aggregated H8 raw difference from {pairs_used_count} pairs.")
        # else: print("  No H8 pairs had overlapping QCU/QCF raw data.") # Optional info
    # else: print("  Missing raw QCU or QCF data for H8.") # Optional info


    # --- Plotting ---
    if not any_diff_data: print("No difference LOESS data available to plot."); plt.close(fig_diff); return

    if np.isfinite(min_diff_overall) and np.isfinite(max_diff_overall): # Limit setting unchanged
        lim_range = max(0.2, max_diff_overall - min_diff_overall); y_lower = min_diff_overall - lim_range * 0.1; y_upper = max_diff_overall + lim_range * 0.1
        if y_lower > -0.05: y_lower = -0.05;
        if y_upper < 0.05: y_upper = 0.05
    else: y_lower, y_upper = -1.0, 1.0

    plot_lines = []; plot_labels = []
    for series_name in ['H8', 'LowBU', 'HighBU']:
        if loess_diff_data.get(series_name):
            data = loess_diff_data[series_name]
            label = f"{series_name} Raw Adjustment (QCF-QCU)" # Updated label
            if series_name in common_station_counts: label += f" (N={common_station_counts[series_name]})"
            elif series_name == 'H8': label += f" (Avg {pairs_used_count} Pairs)" # Indicate source
            line, = ax_diff.plot(data['years'], data['difference'], color=colors[series_name], linestyle='-', linewidth=settings_dict['qcu_linewidth_smooth'], alpha=0.9)
            plot_lines.append(line); plot_labels.append(label)

    ax_diff.set_title(f"Smoothed GHCN Raw Temp Adjustment (QCF - QCU)", fontsize=14, weight='bold', color='white') # Updated title
    ax_diff.set_xlabel("Year", fontsize=12, color='white'); ax_diff.set_ylabel("Avg Temp Difference (°C)", fontsize=12, color='white') # Updated Y label
    ax_diff.tick_params(axis='x', colors='white'); ax_diff.tick_params(axis='y', colors='white')
    ax_diff.set_xlim(min_year_overall, max_year_overall); ax_diff.set_ylim(y_lower, y_upper)
    ax_diff.grid(True, alpha=0.3, color='gray'); ax_diff.axhline(0, color='white', linestyle='--', linewidth=1.0, alpha=0.7)
    if plot_lines: ax_diff.legend(plot_lines, plot_labels, loc='best', fontsize=9, facecolor='black', edgecolor='white')

    # Update footnotes for Difference Plot
    fig_diff.text(0.01, -0.04,
             f"Data: GHCN v4 QCF - QCU | LOESS frac={settings_dict['smoothing_frac']}\n"
             f"Plot shows smoothed difference between QCF and QCU *raw yearly average temperatures*.\n" # Clarified
             f"LowBU/HighBU based on stations common to both QCU/QCF filtered results (N in legend).\n"
             f"H8 based on average of pairwise QCF-QCU raw temperature differences.", # Clarified
             fontsize=8.5, color='white', va='top')

    try: fig_diff.savefig(plot_filename, dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight', facecolor='black'); print(f"Difference plot saved as {plot_filename}")
    except Exception as e: print(f"\nError saving difference plot {plot_filename}: {e}")
    plt.show(); plt.close(fig_diff)

if "QCU" in processed_data and "QCF" in processed_data:
    qcu_ok = any(processed_data["QCU"]['counts'].get(s, 0) > 0 for s in ['H8', 'LowBU', 'HighBU'])
    qcf_ok = any(processed_data["QCF"]['counts'].get(s, 0) > 0 for s in ['H8', 'LowBU', 'HighBU'])
    raw_qcu_ok = raw_data_frames.get("QCU") is not None and not raw_data_frames["QCU"].empty
    raw_qcf_ok = raw_data_frames.get("QCF") is not None and not raw_data_frames["QCF"].empty

    if qcu_ok and qcf_ok: # Check if anomaly results exist for comparison
        plot_comparison( processed_data["QCU"], processed_data["QCF"], settings, os.path.join(output_dir, "ghcn_us_qcu_vs_qcf_comparison.png") )
        if raw_qcu_ok and raw_qcf_ok: # Check if raw data exists for difference plot
             plot_difference( raw_data_frames["QCU"], raw_data_frames["QCF"], processed_data["QCU"], processed_data["QCF"], settings, os.path.join(output_dir, "ghcn_us_qcf_minus_qcu_difference.png") )
        else: print("\nSkipping difference plot: Missing raw QCU or QCF data.")
    else: print("\nSkipping comparison and difference plots: Missing anomaly results for QCU or QCF.")
else: print("\nSkipping comparison and difference plots: Missing processed data structure for QCU or QCF.")

print("\n--- Script Finished ---")
